# Bin/elt/ee-target.env.example — sample EE target config.
#
# Copy to ./Bin/elt/ee-target.env (gitignore that copy) and edit for your
#   DEV/TEST EJBCA-EE instance.
#
# Sourced by ./Bin/5.7-smoke-test.sh when
#   shell env vars aren't already set — the "Desktop App use case" path here:
#
# ./Docs/ejbca-ce-task-5.7-smoke-test-plan.md §1.


# - Server access:
#   Paths are interpreted relative to the project root (where 5.7-smoke-test.sh
#   changes directory to). Absolute paths also work.

ELT_HOST=ejbca-ee-test.your-domain.example
ELT_PORT=443


# - mTLS: Client cert + key: mTLS authentication to the EE REST/SOAP endpoints.
ELT_CERT=./Creds/elt/ee-eltadmin.crt
ELT_KEY=./Creds/elt/ee-eltadmin.key


# - SSL/TLS: CA chain:
#   -> uncomment if the EE host's server cert isn't issued by a CA
#      already trusted by the system.
#   -> Eg: Let's Encrypt, corporate CA already in the OS trust store, etc.

## ELT_CA_CERT=./Creds/elt/your-issuer-ca.crt


